13/04/2010
BELGRADE, Serbia -- Chairman of the National Bank of Serbia's (NBS) supervisory council Dejan Soskic is the ruling coalition's candidate for governor of the financial institution, Prime Minister Mirko Cvetkovic said on Monday (April 12th).
His nomination will require parliamentary approval.
Cvetkovic notes that Soskic, 43, has no political affiliation and solid work experience at the bank.
NBS Governor Radovan Jelasic resigned last month for personal reasons.
(Tanjug, B92, RTS, Beta - 12/04/10)
